5 NEW SECTION. SECTION 2. DECOMMISSIONING LIEN. (1) FOR A WIND GENERATION FACILITY OR SOLAR
6 FACILITY THAT HAS NOT SUBMITTED A BOND TO THE DEPARTMENT OR WITHIN 30 DAYS OF ABANDONMENT OF A WIND
7 GENERATION FACILITY OR SOLAR FACILITY, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL FILE A LIEN ON THE GENERATION ASSETS OF THE
8 FACILITY IN AN AMOUNT NOT LESS THAN THE ESTIMATED DECOMMISSIONING COSTS IN THE DECOMMISSIONING PLAN FILED
9 PURSUANT TO 75-26-304 PLUS AN ANNUAL INFLATIONARY AMOUNT DETERMINED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
10 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL RELEASE A LIEN SECURED PURSUANT TO SUBSECTION (1) FOLLOWING THE
11 RECEIPT AND ACCEPTANCE OF A DECOMMISSIONING BOND SUBMITTED AS REQUIRED BY 75-26-304(6)(B), (6)(C), OR
12 (6)(D).
13 (3) IF THE OWNER OF A WIND GENERATION FACILITY OR SOLAR FACILITY FAILS TO PROPERLY
14 DECOMMISSION A WIND GENERATION FACILITY OR SOLAR FACILITY AND THE OWNER HAS NOT COMMENCED ACTION TO
15 RECTIFY DEFICIENCIES WITHIN 90 DAYS AFTER NOTICE BY THE DEPARTMENT, THE DEPARTMENT MAY FORECLOSE ON THE
16 LIEN. THE DEPARTMENT, THROUGH DEPARTMENT STAFF, EQUIPMENT, RESOURCES, AND MATERIAL UNDER ITS CONTROL
17 OR A CONTRACT WITH OTHERS, MAY TAKE ANY ACTION NECESSARY TO DECOMMISSION THE WIND GENERATION FACILITY
18 OR SOLAR FACILITY.
